50|$|Stroughter {{spent over}} a decade in the minors before making his <b>big</b> <b>league</b> debut on April 7, {{at the age of}} 30. Pinch-hitting for Jim Essian, Stroughter {{grounded}} out in his first <b>big</b> <b>league</b> at-bat, which was against Doug Corbett of the Minnesota Twins.|$|R
